Best part of the whole dang process + details #tamakiquilts

Finished this one yesterday. It’s made out of only material I had on hand. The fabric is mostly from clothing mock-ups. The embroidery was done as a daily diary (Nov 2022-Mar 2023). 🪡 I got really tired in 2022, working on two big projects simultaneously. I had a lot of decision fatigue. I just wanted to let the material guide the outcome. In that way the diary aspect ultimately felt burdensome hence me flipping it to the inside. The end result looks really topographic which is kinda cool. Ty @dylanglynn.mov for modeling! #tamakiquilts

Now open: “Gutters Are Elastic” at @nanaimoartgallery in Nanaimo, BC. My collab w @magiclanterns is in the show, along with my “Blue” quilt, which I made in quarantine/2020 (with some input some of you!). 

Show runs until Sept 24. Info below 🎈

“Gutters Are Elastic is a group exhibition that takes an expanded view on what comics and graphic novels can be: amorphous and empowering things that don’t sit still. This project sees the gutter (the space between the frames in a comic) as a generative site of possibilities where readers insert their own perspectives. This elastic gutter centers the margins, while stretching the story off the page and into the physical space of the Gallery. From ceramic busts to handmade quilts, visitors experience artworks that are linked to comics and graphic novels through a wide range of media. The exhibition features artists from diverse backgrounds and perspectives including Sonny Assu, Shary Boyle, Whess Harman, bailey macabre, Cole Pauls, Jillian Tamaki, Momoko Usami & Joshua W. Cotter, and Ronald Wimberly.”

ROAMING’s final art was completed digitally, but there is still a lot of physical material that was generated during production. Thought I’d show some in the lead up to pub day on Sept 12 😱 These are some initial character sketches, drawn and written. A lot changed (aka names) but a lot is the same too. Tbh I don’t spend too much time visually developing characters, it’s most important they look different from one another. In this early sketch I think Dani and Zoe look too similar, even with the hair difference.

More process: thumbnails. We pitched this book in 2019 or early 2020… by the time i was starting thumbnails, Covid was in full force. I really didn’t want to make a fun comic about travel. Who knew if we’d ever travel again anyway? I got back to them a few months later. I remember doing a lot of these at my parents’ house on their couch.
Materials tests… for the 2 weeks I thought I might do ROAMING traditionally lol. Plus a colour digital printout test. The finals were done in Photoshop and Procreate (iPad)
The original for this was auctioned off for an environmental charity long ago (crummy quality 2nd slide) but I still have the pencils ✏️

Stopped by the @calgarylibrary central branch and was super surprised to see these old FFWD magazines I did covers for in like… 2004? 

Alt weeklies were a big part of my income when I started out. I’m grateful for them and bummed most have fallen away. I miss them. 

Anyway. Amazing amazing collection of local publications all open for perusing. Check it out if you’re into that sort of thing. 

@marikotamaki and I are at @wordfest, our events are on Sunday.
